<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6482] Revamp the vti demo to look and behave more like the other demos.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6482</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The VTI demo began as a set of classes which could not be compiled by the normal build because they used Java 5 features. We hooked these classes into the ordinary build later on (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3684&quot; title=&quot;Wire the vti demo into the build.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3684&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3684&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). But the VTI  demo still sticks out like a sore thumb. We ought to be able to make the VTI demo behave like the other demos now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
